1
00:00:03,925 --> 00:00:04,893
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:04,893 --> 00:00:06,294
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:06,294 --> 00:00:07,362
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

4
00:00:15,403 --> 00:00:16,671
How refreshing.

5
00:00:16,671 --> 00:00:19,040
That fertilizer smell.

6
00:00:19,040 --> 00:00:19,975
Goodness.

7
00:00:20,675 --> 00:00:22,344
Seriously, what am I doing here?

8
00:00:27,816 --> 00:00:28,616
What?

9
00:00:33,054 --> 00:00:33,888
My goodness.

10
00:00:36,825 --> 00:00:38,393
No cabbage.

11
00:00:38,860 --> 00:00:41,529
No cabbage. Unbelievable.

12
00:00:42,998 --> 00:00:44,432
No cabbage.

13
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:46,801
No cabbage.

14
00:00:48,303 --> 00:00:49,971
What brings you here without notice?

15
00:00:51,039 --> 00:00:53,608
I came because I had something urgent
to tell you.

16
00:01:04,619 --> 00:01:05,587
I'm sorry.

17
00:01:05,587 --> 00:01:07,589
It's my fault for neglecting the field.

18
00:01:09,090 --> 00:01:10,525
Not at all.

19
00:01:10,525 --> 00:01:12,127
You're doing a great job, Mr. Seong.

20
00:01:13,061 --> 00:01:14,596
You're doing more than enough...

21
00:01:15,063 --> 00:01:16,298
for Mat Story.

22
00:01:20,302 --> 00:01:23,371
Cover your noses.
The smell is overwhelming.

23
00:01:23,772 --> 00:01:26,574
Is Mat Story planning
to pull something again?

24
00:01:27,575 --> 00:01:31,012
Things seem pretty complicated
for Mr. Seong.

25
00:01:32,180 --> 00:01:34,149
By the way, that man...

26
00:01:35,150 --> 00:01:36,785
looks familiar.

27
00:01:37,719 --> 00:01:39,354
I've got a bad feeling about this.

28
00:01:42,324 --> 00:01:43,925
So...

29
00:01:44,459 --> 00:01:47,829
there are new instructions
from the executive director.

30
00:01:48,797 --> 00:01:50,198
Here in Yeonri-ri,

31
00:01:51,566 --> 00:01:54,903
our company's new vision will take shape.

32
00:01:55,837 --> 00:01:56,738
We want you,

33
00:01:57,639 --> 00:01:59,541
Mr. Seong, to carry it out yourself.

34
00:01:59,841 --> 00:02:03,545
With those hands that have only
ever worked on cabbage for Mat Story...

35
00:02:04,145 --> 00:02:06,815
In your name, Seong Tae Hun.

36
00:02:06,815 --> 00:02:09,517
Isn't that job about researching
and developing cabbage?

37
00:02:30,839 --> 00:02:31,773
Unbelievable.

38
00:02:34,509 --> 00:02:35,410
Take this.

39
00:02:36,177 --> 00:02:37,345
Come on.

40
00:02:37,646 --> 00:02:38,747
What is this?

41
00:02:38,980 --> 00:02:41,950
You'll hear it from Mr. Bae
when you see him.

42
00:02:42,717 --> 00:02:44,219
Mr. Choi.

43
00:02:44,219 --> 00:02:45,654
Why did you really come here?

44
00:02:47,455 --> 00:02:49,591
I came here to work.

45
00:02:49,591 --> 00:02:50,925
Let's work.

46
00:02:52,761 --> 00:02:54,129
Let's work.

47
00:02:55,163 --> 00:02:57,065
Don't those people ever move away?

48
00:02:57,065 --> 00:02:58,366
I'm so sick of them.

49
00:02:58,366 --> 00:02:59,968
They didn't recognize me, did they?

50
00:02:59,968 --> 00:03:02,437
Move the car.

51
00:03:09,077 --> 00:03:14,249
(EP 7 Life is a Tightrope Walk)

52
00:03:14,249 --> 00:03:16,184
(Analysis Report)

53
00:03:17,619 --> 00:03:20,121
(Chlorpyrifos, imidacloprid, fail)

54
00:03:29,130 --> 00:03:30,665
(Lead, cadmium, arsenic,
mercury, fail)

55
00:03:30,665 --> 00:03:32,801
What is this?

56
00:03:33,568 --> 00:03:34,436
What's this?

57
00:03:35,370 --> 00:03:36,471
This is ridiculous.

58
00:03:43,445 --> 00:03:44,346
What is it?

59
00:03:45,613 --> 00:03:48,850
Fail, fail...

60
00:03:48,850 --> 00:03:50,385
It's nothing but failures.

61
00:03:50,385 --> 00:03:53,455
Do they go to jail if they write "pass"?

62
00:03:55,924 --> 00:03:56,925
So you'll be fired?

63
00:03:57,892 --> 00:03:59,594
How does this make sense?

64
00:03:59,794 --> 00:04:01,930
These numbers can't be right.

65
00:04:01,930 --> 00:04:03,298
You know what I did.

66
00:04:03,298 --> 00:04:05,767
I only used natural fertilizer
and cow manure.

67
00:04:05,767 --> 00:04:07,068
Does this make any sense?

68
00:04:08,703 --> 00:04:09,604
Let me see it.

69
00:04:11,439 --> 00:04:14,609
They gave me a paper like this
when they rejected my cabbage.

70
00:04:17,579 --> 00:04:21,116
Lead, cadmium, and nitrate nitrogen.
Exceeded limits.

71
00:04:21,116 --> 00:04:23,151
Wow. Word for word.

72
00:04:23,151 --> 00:04:24,819
Unbelievable.

73
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:26,488
Goodness.

74
00:04:26,755 --> 00:04:30,492
Back then, they never told me
whether to use pesticides or not.

75
00:04:30,959 --> 00:04:31,726
But think about it.

76
00:04:31,726 --> 00:04:34,296
How are you supposed to farm
without pesticides?

77
00:04:34,696 --> 00:04:38,366
They even said they'd help me
turn it into a local special product,

78
00:04:38,366 --> 00:04:42,070
so I used those expensive
eco-friendly pesticides.

79
00:04:42,070 --> 00:04:45,240
But they said they found lead
and cadmium in my cabbage.

80
00:04:50,011 --> 00:04:52,881
And none of you proved it otherwise?

81
00:04:56,584 --> 00:04:58,787
So if I can't disprove
these results either...

82
00:05:07,362 --> 00:05:11,099
How can someone working for a company
ever beat their boss?

83
00:05:11,099 --> 00:05:11,933
Even so...

84
00:05:14,302 --> 00:05:15,236
Do your best.

85
00:05:16,371 --> 00:05:17,238
I'm off.

86
00:05:30,885 --> 00:05:33,288
This isn't right.

87
00:05:34,222 --> 00:05:35,123
The test...

88
00:05:37,592 --> 00:05:38,593
I'll run it again myself.

89
00:05:51,239 --> 00:05:52,140
You...

90
00:05:52,874 --> 00:05:55,176
How can you do this to me?

91
00:05:55,176 --> 00:05:56,544
- Do you know...
- Honey.

92
00:05:56,544 --> 00:05:59,180
- who this is because of?
- Honey.

93
00:05:59,180 --> 00:06:00,649
Apologize to Mom, Ji Cheon.

94
00:06:00,649 --> 00:06:02,317
Honey.

95
00:06:02,317 --> 00:06:05,487
- Do you know who's keeping me alive?
- Honey, calm down.

96
00:06:05,487 --> 00:06:07,756
- What am I supposed to do?
- Calm down.

97
00:06:07,756 --> 00:06:08,623
Honey.

98
00:06:11,459 --> 00:06:12,294
Honey.

99
00:06:14,329 --> 00:06:16,531
Honey, what's wrong?

100
00:06:16,531 --> 00:06:18,600
Honey.

101
00:06:37,752 --> 00:06:39,020
Is he okay?

102
00:06:46,828 --> 00:06:48,330
Ji Cheon, are you okay?

103
00:06:50,432 --> 00:06:51,299
I'll do it.

104
00:07:09,718 --> 00:07:12,621
How can you do this to me?

105
00:07:12,621 --> 00:07:14,522
Seong Ji Cheon.

106
00:07:17,459 --> 00:07:18,326
No.

107
00:07:19,094 --> 00:07:21,162
No way. Whose son is Ji Cheon?

108
00:07:21,596 --> 00:07:23,999
Even during puberty,
when all other teenagers act out,

109
00:07:24,499 --> 00:07:26,301
he never caused a single problem.

110
00:07:26,668 --> 00:07:27,902
He dropped out without telling us?

111
00:07:28,503 --> 00:07:30,705
When he knows how hard I worked
to raise him?

112
00:07:31,473 --> 00:07:32,374
That's a lie.

113
00:07:33,108 --> 00:07:34,075
Yes.

114
00:07:35,377 --> 00:07:36,277
Let's verify it.

115
00:07:37,278 --> 00:07:38,179
I'll check with the school.

116
00:07:38,980 --> 00:07:40,181
Yes, check it.

117
00:07:41,883 --> 00:07:43,952
Yes. Hold on.

118
00:07:44,219 --> 00:07:45,020
Yes.

119
00:07:45,220 --> 00:07:47,088
(Hangook University)

120
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,928
Hello.

121
00:07:54,396 --> 00:07:55,930
So...

122
00:07:56,865 --> 00:07:58,667
this is the administration office
of Hangook University, right?

123
00:08:16,618 --> 00:08:19,220
Dad, is Mom okay? Can we go home?

124
00:08:20,588 --> 00:08:21,356
Cho Mi Ryeo.

125
00:08:29,397 --> 00:08:30,265
Honey.

126
00:08:34,235 --> 00:08:35,804
Honey. Cho Mi Ryeo. I'm coming in.

127
00:08:38,273 --> 00:08:39,107
Where did she go?

128
00:08:41,276 --> 00:08:42,877
- You're home early.
- You scared me.

129
00:08:44,145 --> 00:08:46,314
You were cleaning?

130
00:08:46,581 --> 00:08:47,449
Yes.

131
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:49,584
How are you feeling?

132
00:08:50,185 --> 00:08:51,753
You should go see a doctor.

133
00:08:53,021 --> 00:08:54,656
Let's go to a general hospital.

134
00:08:54,656 --> 00:08:57,759
You should get properly checked out.

135
00:08:57,759 --> 00:09:00,729
I'm not terminally ill, so don't treat me
like a patient.

136
00:09:01,262 --> 00:09:02,897
That's not what I meant.

137
00:09:03,465 --> 00:09:04,666
We could get some fresh air
while we're at it...

138
00:09:04,666 --> 00:09:07,969
and just a simple consultation.

139
00:09:09,204 --> 00:09:10,905
I didn't know about it.

140
00:09:11,573 --> 00:09:13,708
It gets better as soon as I take the meds.

141
00:09:13,708 --> 00:09:15,276
I've experienced it many times already.

142
00:09:15,810 --> 00:09:18,647
You still should've told me.

143
00:09:20,815 --> 00:09:22,150
Would it have made things better
if I told you?

144
00:09:24,319 --> 00:09:27,789
It must've been tough in Canada
all by yourself.

145
00:09:27,789 --> 00:09:29,391
That's why you get these panic attacks.

146
00:09:30,392 --> 00:09:31,860
As for Ji Cheon,

147
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:34,896
I was trying to handle it
before you found out.

148
00:09:34,896 --> 00:09:37,499
I didn't mean to hide it from you.

149
00:09:37,932 --> 00:09:40,869
Forget it. I'll handle
Ji Cheon's issue myself.

150
00:09:43,438 --> 00:09:44,239
Right.

151
00:09:45,006 --> 00:09:48,310
Ji Cheon's request to drop out
hasn't gone through yet.

152
00:09:48,943 --> 00:09:52,047
I called the school earlier.

153
00:09:52,047 --> 00:09:54,516
I guess he still has to meet
with the department head.

154
00:09:54,516 --> 00:09:56,217
So there's still a chance.

155
00:09:57,719 --> 00:10:01,790
Still... I think you should talk
to Ji Cheon.

156
00:10:01,790 --> 00:10:02,657
Honey.

157
00:10:03,491 --> 00:10:06,895
Do you really not understand
what Ji Cheon means to me?

158
00:10:08,129 --> 00:10:10,832
He should be sitting in a doctor's coat.

159
00:10:10,832 --> 00:10:13,068
But instead, he's in a cafeteria
wearing an apron.

160
00:10:13,702 --> 00:10:15,236
How am I supposed to watch that?

161
00:10:15,236 --> 00:10:17,505
Watching my son's life fall apart...

162
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:21,409
It is all because of this environment.

163
00:10:21,409 --> 00:10:22,610
Once he goes back to Seoul,

164
00:10:22,610 --> 00:10:24,646
he'll change for sure.

165
00:10:24,646 --> 00:10:26,147
All right, honey. For now...

166
00:10:26,147 --> 00:10:28,283
Calm down. Relax.

167
00:10:28,283 --> 00:10:29,851
I don't want you to collapse again.

168
00:10:33,488 --> 00:10:34,356
Take a deep breath.

169
00:10:51,906 --> 00:10:52,741
What's wrong?

170
00:10:53,742 --> 00:10:56,378
There are still mosquitoes around.

171
00:10:56,378 --> 00:10:57,512
I got bitten.

172
00:10:58,046 --> 00:10:59,014
Be careful.

173
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:02,350
Okay.

174
00:11:06,621 --> 00:11:07,622
All day,

175
00:11:09,491 --> 00:11:12,360
your mind's been elsewhere.
I'm right here, though.

176
00:11:15,230 --> 00:11:16,131
I'm sorry.

177
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,368
Is your mom really upset?

178
00:11:24,105 --> 00:11:25,006
It's understandable.

179
00:11:26,474 --> 00:11:29,344
I quit med school, but I don't have
any other plans.

180
00:11:30,679 --> 00:11:32,147
Telling her I'll figure it out slowly...

181
00:11:32,947 --> 00:11:34,649
Maybe I'm just being selfish.

182
00:11:37,552 --> 00:11:39,020
It must be tough for you.

183
00:11:40,522 --> 00:11:42,857
Get everything off your chest
by telling me. I'll hear you out.

184
00:11:42,857 --> 00:11:45,627
I'm basically your personal
bamboo forest, right?

185
00:11:46,361 --> 00:11:48,296
Or do you want to go for a run together
to our usual spot?

186
00:11:48,296 --> 00:11:49,230
Get some fresh air?

187
00:11:50,598 --> 00:11:51,666
Bo Mi.

188
00:11:52,334 --> 00:11:54,569
I'm not so good with multitasking.

189
00:11:56,137 --> 00:11:59,240
Please give me some time.

190
00:13:04,139 --> 00:13:05,373
Mom.

191
00:13:07,275 --> 00:13:08,410
Dr. Seong.

192
00:13:09,444 --> 00:13:10,845
You must be hungry.

193
00:13:11,012 --> 00:13:12,480
Dinner is almost ready.

194
00:13:12,781 --> 00:13:15,650
I made your favorite, bulgogi.

195
00:13:23,825 --> 00:13:25,860
This has protein...

196
00:13:25,860 --> 00:13:27,562
and this has iron.

197
00:13:28,330 --> 00:13:30,265
If you're going to study,

198
00:13:30,265 --> 00:13:33,168
you need to eat well and properly.

199
00:13:33,168 --> 00:13:34,202
Eat up.

200
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:36,805
Mom.

201
00:13:36,805 --> 00:13:39,507
Why are you acting like that?
You're scaring me.

202
00:13:40,375 --> 00:13:41,977
Is there something wrong with you?

203
00:13:43,645 --> 00:13:44,479
Here.

204
00:13:45,046 --> 00:13:47,949
Dr. Seong, eat up.

205
00:13:48,216 --> 00:13:50,185
I'm sorry.

206
00:13:50,185 --> 00:13:52,721
I've been so busy taking care
of Ji Sang and Ji Gu...

207
00:13:52,721 --> 00:13:54,522
that I didn't know
how much you were struggling.

208
00:13:56,758 --> 00:13:58,593
You should eat too, honey.

209
00:13:59,728 --> 00:14:00,562
Ji Cheon.

210
00:14:01,196 --> 00:14:03,865
Will you be my guardian tomorrow?

211
00:14:18,546 --> 00:14:19,314
Honey.

212
00:14:20,448 --> 00:14:22,250
Are you going to see a doctor?
Are you okay?

213
00:14:23,551 --> 00:14:25,820
Why do you keep asking me that?

214
00:14:30,458 --> 00:14:31,693
You're acting strange right now.

215
00:14:31,693 --> 00:14:34,629
Just get angry instead.

216
00:14:34,629 --> 00:14:36,398
I have no idea what you're up to.

217
00:14:38,166 --> 00:14:41,136
That's your problem.

218
00:14:41,603 --> 00:14:43,805
You don't know anything.

219
00:14:46,408 --> 00:14:47,242
That's right.

220
00:14:48,410 --> 00:14:50,345
I don't know anything. I admit it.

221
00:14:50,345 --> 00:14:51,946
So...

222
00:14:52,547 --> 00:14:54,149
tell me.

223
00:14:55,317 --> 00:14:56,718
Let's talk.

224
00:14:57,552 --> 00:14:58,453
Okay?

225
00:14:58,453 --> 00:15:00,388
Let's think this through together
and find a solution.

226
00:15:02,424 --> 00:15:05,694
I handled Ji Cheon's issue
the wrong way, so...

227
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:12,567
Yeah?

228
00:15:13,935 --> 00:15:14,769
You want me to tell you?

229
00:15:17,706 --> 00:15:20,008
How do you think I lived
in Canada for three years?

230
00:15:20,775 --> 00:15:23,411
Everyone told me that I was lucky.

231
00:15:23,812 --> 00:15:27,015
A husband who's a corporate manager,
and a son in med school.

232
00:15:27,549 --> 00:15:29,117
But would they know?

233
00:15:29,117 --> 00:15:30,719
How hard it is to raise three kids...

234
00:15:30,719 --> 00:15:32,887
on that corporate manager's salary?

235
00:15:32,887 --> 00:15:35,323
That's why I had to take money from...

236
00:15:39,361 --> 00:15:41,830
I never even bought myself proper clothes.

237
00:15:41,830 --> 00:15:44,299
My hands would tremble
every time I tried to buy anything.

238
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:46,735
Forget it.

239
00:15:47,268 --> 00:15:49,337
You don't need to think of ways to help.

240
00:15:49,804 --> 00:15:52,307
Just focus on going back to headquarters.

241
00:15:55,577 --> 00:15:56,978
If we stay here longer,

242
00:15:57,479 --> 00:15:59,981
I'm afraid I'll lose my son.

243
00:16:02,684 --> 00:16:05,687
Going back to Seoul won't solve anything.

244
00:16:06,154 --> 00:16:08,623
If we go back to Seoul,
will Ji Cheon become a doctor?

245
00:16:09,391 --> 00:16:11,326
I know how you feel,

246
00:16:12,027 --> 00:16:15,263
but you really need to hear Ji Cheon out.

247
00:16:19,034 --> 00:16:19,934
Ji Cheon...

248
00:16:21,369 --> 00:16:23,171
would never fail to understand
what I want.

249
00:16:24,406 --> 00:16:26,508
Do you think I raised him to be an idiot?

250
00:16:29,044 --> 00:16:32,080
Yes, he might be lost for a moment.

251
00:16:34,482 --> 00:16:36,084
But I can convince him.

252
00:16:51,566 --> 00:16:52,701
Bo Mi.

253
00:16:53,268 --> 00:16:55,537
I'm not so good with multitasking.

254
00:16:57,138 --> 00:17:00,175
Please give me some time.

255
00:17:01,076 --> 00:17:01,977
Time?

256
00:17:07,115 --> 00:17:08,183
Time for what?

257
00:17:11,853 --> 00:17:12,821
No.

258
00:17:13,288 --> 00:17:15,123
Ji Cheon may need some time...

259
00:17:15,123 --> 00:17:18,226
because he's in
a really difficult situation right now.

260
00:17:19,427 --> 00:17:21,896
But at the beginning of a relationship,
every second counts.

261
00:17:21,896 --> 00:17:23,598
Taking some time right now...

262
00:17:23,598 --> 00:17:24,799
Does it mean we're doomed?

263
00:17:26,267 --> 00:17:27,168
What do I do?

264
00:17:31,973 --> 00:17:33,642
Should I go over right now to talk?

265
00:17:35,243 --> 00:17:38,346
No. He asked for time,

266
00:17:38,913 --> 00:17:39,948
so I should wait.

267
00:17:44,252 --> 00:17:45,020
Wait.

268
00:17:46,354 --> 00:17:47,389
Wait, Im Bo Mi.

269
00:17:50,492 --> 00:17:51,493
Wait, Im Bo Mi.

270
00:18:14,683 --> 00:18:16,151
Seeing someone come down
from headquarters...

271
00:18:16,918 --> 00:18:18,887
tells me something is bound to happen.

272
00:18:21,957 --> 00:18:25,260
What if Seong Tae Hun is fired?

273
00:18:29,130 --> 00:18:30,231
That's not good.

274
00:18:30,999 --> 00:18:32,968
If neither I nor the cabbage grows,

275
00:18:33,501 --> 00:18:34,903
Dad will be sad.

276
00:18:35,670 --> 00:18:37,939
I'll grit my teeth...

277
00:18:38,506 --> 00:18:39,574
and push through.

278
00:18:40,075 --> 00:18:42,610
I will get through this no matter what
and go back.

279
00:18:42,610 --> 00:18:44,813
Back to my position at Mat Story in Seoul.

280
00:18:46,481 --> 00:18:48,016
Forget cabbage.

281
00:18:49,617 --> 00:18:52,487
I hope he doesn't end up
out on the street with his sons.

282
00:19:21,650 --> 00:19:26,454
(No new notifications)

283
00:19:26,855 --> 00:19:28,757
Is it that serious?

284
00:19:29,824 --> 00:19:31,726
He hasn't called at all.

285
00:19:52,314 --> 00:19:53,181
Bo Mi.

286
00:19:53,648 --> 00:19:56,151
I won't be able to go to work
for a few days.

287
00:19:56,384 --> 00:19:57,218
I'm sorry.

288
00:20:52,407 --> 00:20:53,274
As expected,

289
00:20:54,309 --> 00:20:55,710
there's nothing wrong with the seedlings.

290
00:21:04,753 --> 00:21:08,556
(Analysis Report)

291
00:21:12,560 --> 00:21:14,562
(Chlorpyrifos, imidacloprid)

292
00:21:14,562 --> 00:21:16,064
I am certain...

293
00:21:17,499 --> 00:21:19,134
these analysis results were manipulated.

294
00:21:21,336 --> 00:21:22,170
So...

295
00:21:22,504 --> 00:21:24,673
if I successfully grow
Mat Story napa cabbage,

296
00:21:24,673 --> 00:21:26,875
does that mean I can return
to headquarters?

297
00:21:28,209 --> 00:21:29,277
Mr. Seong Tae Hun.

298
00:21:31,279 --> 00:21:32,380
Go to Yeonri-ri...

299
00:21:33,348 --> 00:21:35,383
and prove your value.

300
00:21:36,851 --> 00:21:38,586
It wasn't Mr. Choi.

301
00:21:38,586 --> 00:21:39,988
This was orchestrated by Mr. Bae
from the beginning.

302
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:48,630
They must know they can't fool me
with a manipulated report like this.

303
00:21:50,065 --> 00:21:51,466
So why...

304
00:21:55,337 --> 00:21:56,705
(Chlorpyrifos, imidacloprid, fail)

305
00:21:56,705 --> 00:21:59,007
What if it's not about forcing me to quit,

306
00:21:59,674 --> 00:22:01,476
but about making sure...

307
00:22:01,476 --> 00:22:03,111
the Yeonri-ri employee fails?

308
00:22:12,587 --> 00:22:16,391
(Yeonri-ri Village Hall)

309
00:22:16,858 --> 00:22:18,893
(Village chief)

310
00:22:21,463 --> 00:22:22,330
Chief.

311
00:22:23,765 --> 00:22:24,733
Were you fired?

312
00:22:24,733 --> 00:22:26,167
No, of course not.

313
00:22:26,167 --> 00:22:28,203
I want to ask you something.

314
00:22:30,405 --> 00:22:31,172
Thank you.

315
00:22:34,576 --> 00:22:38,546
The Mat Story manager
you told me about before...

316
00:22:38,546 --> 00:22:40,048
Have you met him, too?

317
00:22:41,750 --> 00:22:43,051
Let's see...

318
00:22:44,819 --> 00:22:45,787
I don't think so.

319
00:22:46,655 --> 00:22:49,291
Other than someone who got demoted
and came and went, I haven't seen anyone.

320
00:22:50,258 --> 00:22:52,360
What about that director
you saw at the field?

321
00:22:52,360 --> 00:22:53,194
Director?

322
00:22:54,029 --> 00:22:56,398
The one with slicked-back hair,

323
00:22:56,398 --> 00:22:58,933
covering his nose with a handkerchief?

324
00:22:58,933 --> 00:22:59,834
That was a director?

325
00:23:00,835 --> 00:23:02,304
When I tried to get a better look,
he ran off.

326
00:23:03,805 --> 00:23:06,741
He's definitely one of those Mat Story men
who came down here before.

327
00:23:07,709 --> 00:23:10,312
Did a lot of Mat Story people
come here before?

328
00:23:11,246 --> 00:23:13,248
At first, several people came and went.

329
00:23:13,515 --> 00:23:16,518
But later, there was only one person
who came and went as the one in charge.

330
00:23:17,619 --> 00:23:18,520
Noh Hyeon Gap.

331
00:23:37,973 --> 00:23:39,107
Wait a second.

332
00:23:56,992 --> 00:24:00,261
(Mat Story Noh Hyeon Gap)

333
00:24:16,378 --> 00:24:17,178
Yes?

334
00:24:17,512 --> 00:24:18,380
Mr. Noh.

335
00:24:18,713 --> 00:24:19,981
You must be very busy.

336
00:24:20,782 --> 00:24:23,918
You didn't even know
I personally went to Yeonri-ri.

337
00:24:24,819 --> 00:24:26,721
You should've called me
if you needed something.

338
00:24:26,721 --> 00:24:27,689
Why did you come yourself?

339
00:24:27,689 --> 00:24:30,492
Mr. Bae insisted multiple times...

340
00:24:30,492 --> 00:24:32,327
that I go myself.

341
00:24:32,861 --> 00:24:34,596
I couldn't reach you,

342
00:24:35,130 --> 00:24:38,433
so I almost got angry.

343
00:24:40,969 --> 00:24:42,470
But after seeing the field,
I let it slide.

344
00:24:43,471 --> 00:24:44,606
Was that your doing?

345
00:24:45,674 --> 00:24:48,009
If you wrecked it,

346
00:24:48,009 --> 00:24:49,778
you should've told us about it.

347
00:24:50,211 --> 00:24:52,113
Then I wouldn't have had
to go there myself.

348
00:24:55,450 --> 00:24:58,053
Do you have more instructions for me?

349
00:24:59,254 --> 00:25:00,221
Seong Tae Hun.

350
00:25:00,755 --> 00:25:02,424
Get him to sign the report.

351
00:25:03,158 --> 00:25:04,392
Do a good job this time.

352
00:25:05,727 --> 00:25:08,964
He won't sign it easily.

353
00:25:12,834 --> 00:25:16,805
Those stubborn farmers
who wouldn't sign anything...

354
00:25:16,805 --> 00:25:18,606
Who's the one that got them to sign?

355
00:25:22,377 --> 00:25:25,513
That's your specialty, Mr. Noh.

356
00:25:25,847 --> 00:25:26,715
Isn't it?

357
00:25:28,583 --> 00:25:29,517
Goodbye.

358
00:25:53,975 --> 00:25:54,843
Mom.

359
00:25:55,176 --> 00:25:57,178
I have something to give you.

360
00:25:58,913 --> 00:26:00,515
How do I look today?

361
00:26:02,183 --> 00:26:04,819
It's been a while since I've gone out
with you, Dr. Seong.

362
00:26:04,819 --> 00:26:07,155
And the weather is very beautiful too.

363
00:26:07,155 --> 00:26:08,023
Mom.

364
00:26:09,057 --> 00:26:11,493
Can you please stop calling me Dr. Seong?

365
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:13,428
Let's go.

366
00:26:13,662 --> 00:26:16,164
I've planned everything out.

367
00:26:16,665 --> 00:26:17,499
Planned what?

368
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:20,435
I thought we were going to the hospital.

369
00:26:21,002 --> 00:26:21,803
Let's go.

370
00:26:24,873 --> 00:26:25,807
Where are we?

371
00:26:26,474 --> 00:26:29,344
Just follow me. I've arranged everything.

372
00:26:30,078 --> 00:26:31,112
Here we are.

373
00:26:31,713 --> 00:26:32,580
Go on in.

374
00:26:35,250 --> 00:26:36,785
Hello.

375
00:26:39,421 --> 00:26:40,622
Well...

376
00:26:40,622 --> 00:26:42,157
Who's getting their hair done?

377
00:26:43,258 --> 00:26:45,327
My eldest son.

378
00:26:46,695 --> 00:26:48,930
Please trim his hair a bit.

379
00:26:48,930 --> 00:26:52,033
We're on our way to Seoul,
so make him look neat.

380
00:26:52,033 --> 00:26:54,703
What? Is he going back to Seoul first?

381
00:26:54,703 --> 00:26:56,137
Of course.

382
00:26:57,038 --> 00:26:58,640
Soon,

383
00:26:58,640 --> 00:27:01,309
he'll need to take the board exam.

384
00:27:01,309 --> 00:27:03,211
He's got a good rest until now.

385
00:27:05,580 --> 00:27:06,514
What are you doing?

386
00:27:11,086 --> 00:27:13,955
Are you going to embarrass me?

387
00:27:15,824 --> 00:27:18,860
Please make him look nice and neat.

388
00:27:18,860 --> 00:27:19,894
Go.

389
00:27:20,662 --> 00:27:22,197
All right. Have a seat here.

390
00:27:22,197 --> 00:27:23,398
I'll wait right here.

391
00:27:24,232 --> 00:27:25,066
Hey.

392
00:27:26,001 --> 00:27:27,902
Does Bo Mi know you're leaving?

393
00:27:30,005 --> 00:27:30,939
Why does Bo Mi need to know?

394
00:27:33,308 --> 00:27:36,311
Because he worked at school part-time
for a little while?

395
00:27:36,911 --> 00:27:38,380
I'm sure she knows.

396
00:27:38,380 --> 00:27:41,182
It's not like he was going
to work there forever.

397
00:27:43,918 --> 00:27:46,288
Should I just shave it all off?

398
00:27:50,792 --> 00:27:53,795
By the way, you're all grown up.

399
00:27:54,496 --> 00:27:56,831
But you still come to get your haircut
with your mom?

400
00:27:57,632 --> 00:28:01,603
Yes, because my son really
looks after his mom.

401
00:28:07,642 --> 00:28:09,210
I'm sorry. I'll be back another time.

402
00:28:11,279 --> 00:28:12,347
Why?

403
00:28:14,816 --> 00:28:17,319
I'm sorry. We'll come back another time.

404
00:28:18,853 --> 00:28:19,988
Seon Ja.

405
00:28:19,988 --> 00:28:20,822
Yes?

406
00:28:20,822 --> 00:28:22,190
Is something wrong with that woman?

407
00:28:23,591 --> 00:28:26,428
She was sitting here twisting her hair.

408
00:28:26,995 --> 00:28:27,862
Right?

409
00:28:29,030 --> 00:28:30,632
What's wrong with her?
She's acting strange.

410
00:28:32,334 --> 00:28:33,468
Come on.

411
00:28:34,069 --> 00:28:35,437
It's not like...

412
00:28:35,937 --> 00:28:38,907
Bo Mi is going to work
at the cafeteria forever.

413
00:28:39,607 --> 00:28:42,911
She dragged her son, a grown man,

414
00:28:42,911 --> 00:28:44,112
- here to tell us that?
- Yes.

415
00:28:44,112 --> 00:28:45,347
- Right?
- Yes.

416
00:28:46,881 --> 00:28:47,682
Seoul?

417
00:28:48,516 --> 00:28:50,919
It's just a bus ride away.

418
00:28:50,919 --> 00:28:53,321
What? Do doctors not eat?

419
00:28:53,888 --> 00:28:56,858
Nutritionists are above doctors.

420
00:28:59,127 --> 00:29:00,595
Hairstylists too.

421
00:29:02,631 --> 00:29:04,165
Why are you getting so angry?

422
00:29:04,633 --> 00:29:06,368
That's not the real issue here.

423
00:29:12,040 --> 00:29:13,274
Dr. Seong.

424
00:29:14,376 --> 00:29:16,011
Once you go back to Seoul,
you'll be so busy...

425
00:29:16,011 --> 00:29:18,246
that we won't get to spend time together.

426
00:29:18,246 --> 00:29:19,147
Mom.

427
00:29:20,315 --> 00:29:22,384
I won't go back to Seoul no matter what.

428
00:29:22,684 --> 00:29:26,988
Just imagining you as Dr. Seong
treating patients...

429
00:29:26,988 --> 00:29:30,792
in your white gown...

430
00:29:30,792 --> 00:29:32,227
makes me smile even in my sleep.

431
00:29:38,333 --> 00:29:39,367
I'm serious.

432
00:29:42,170 --> 00:29:43,538
Ji Cheon.

433
00:29:44,439 --> 00:29:45,774
Ji Cheon.

434
00:29:46,374 --> 00:29:47,309
Ji Cheon.

435
00:30:07,195 --> 00:30:09,631
I'm sorry for deciding this on my own.

436
00:30:11,466 --> 00:30:13,435
Every moment up until now
felt like a breaking point.

437
00:30:15,437 --> 00:30:17,072
For the first time in my life,

438
00:30:17,973 --> 00:30:19,407
I've made a decision on my own.

439
00:30:21,009 --> 00:30:23,078
I'm quitting med school, Dad.

440
00:30:24,012 --> 00:30:24,846
What?

441
00:30:25,647 --> 00:30:28,550
I never once wanted to become a doctor.

442
00:30:30,051 --> 00:30:31,886
I just decided to do it
because you and Mom wanted me to.

443
00:30:33,054 --> 00:30:34,122
I was pushed into it.

444
00:30:38,326 --> 00:30:39,260
Gauze.

445
00:30:39,260 --> 00:30:40,128
Suction, quickly.

446
00:30:44,132 --> 00:30:45,467
Ji Cheon.

447
00:30:47,302 --> 00:30:50,205
I tried my best to hold on,

448
00:30:51,539 --> 00:30:52,407
but the truth is,

449
00:30:52,907 --> 00:30:54,309
I was wavering every day.

450
00:30:58,013 --> 00:31:00,048
I'm finding my way onto the right path.

451
00:31:01,182 --> 00:31:03,251
I'll prove it with results.

452
00:31:07,589 --> 00:31:09,758
Every night I told myself I was okay,

453
00:31:10,625 --> 00:31:12,227
but I was afraid of facing the next day.

454
00:31:15,063 --> 00:31:16,731
I wanted to lean on my family,

455
00:31:17,732 --> 00:31:18,867
but I couldn't say anything...

456
00:31:19,868 --> 00:31:21,236
because I was afraid of disappointing you.

457
00:31:28,910 --> 00:31:31,680
I know this might seem
like a selfish choice.

458
00:31:33,248 --> 00:31:34,616
But for now,

459
00:31:36,951 --> 00:31:39,220
I just want to learn how to breathe again.

460
00:31:42,924 --> 00:31:45,193
You may not understand
my decision right now,

461
00:31:46,261 --> 00:31:47,662
but I hope you can know that...

462
00:31:48,596 --> 00:31:50,865
I'm not running away.

463
00:31:51,232 --> 00:31:52,701
That I'm just trying to walk
my own path slowly.

464
00:32:13,955 --> 00:32:16,992
But later, there was only one person
who came and went as the one in charge.

465
00:32:17,759 --> 00:32:18,627
Noh Hyeon Gap.

466
00:32:25,467 --> 00:32:26,768
The inspector's last name is Noh.

467
00:32:29,604 --> 00:32:31,306
The name of the one in charge
is Noh Hyeon Gap.

468
00:32:33,475 --> 00:32:34,342
I'm sorry.

469
00:32:35,877 --> 00:32:36,911
I can't make...

470
00:32:38,146 --> 00:32:39,214
the same mistake twice.

471
00:32:41,616 --> 00:32:42,684
The manager...

472
00:32:44,019 --> 00:32:46,721
The person in charge of
the Yeonri-ri project was Noh Hyeon Gap.

473
00:32:48,023 --> 00:32:50,558
But the project failed a long time ago,

474
00:32:50,558 --> 00:32:52,260
and he's not even
a Mat Story employee anymore.

475
00:32:52,260 --> 00:32:53,962
So why is he still working under Mr. Choi?

476
00:32:55,897 --> 00:32:58,233
What is Mr. Choi up to?

477
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:20,789
Mr. Noh Hyeon Gap?

478
00:33:25,060 --> 00:33:26,227
You're Mr. Noh Hyeon Gap, right?

479
00:33:28,430 --> 00:33:31,099
The person in charge of
the Yeonri-ri project back then.

480
00:33:31,099 --> 00:33:33,768
And now the fake field manager
of Mat Story.

481
00:33:37,706 --> 00:33:38,974
Who are you, really?

482
00:33:40,308 --> 00:33:42,777
What have you been doing on this land
for nearly ten years?

483
00:33:45,680 --> 00:33:47,082
Sign the document...

484
00:33:48,750 --> 00:33:49,851
sent down from the company.

485
00:33:52,287 --> 00:33:54,122
Did Mr. Choi order you to do this?

486
00:33:54,122 --> 00:33:56,091
You better cooperate.

487
00:33:56,091 --> 00:33:56,958
No.

488
00:33:57,626 --> 00:33:59,327
I can't do that.

489
00:33:59,327 --> 00:34:01,262
No, I won't do it.

490
00:34:02,430 --> 00:34:04,599
I can't sign my name, Seong Tae Hun,

491
00:34:04,966 --> 00:34:07,302
on some recklessly fabricated document.

492
00:34:08,436 --> 00:34:10,639
You won't have a choice either.

493
00:34:10,639 --> 00:34:11,506
In the end,

494
00:34:13,608 --> 00:34:14,676
you'll sign it.

495
00:34:16,845 --> 00:34:17,679
No.

496
00:34:18,546 --> 00:34:20,415
I'm not like you.

497
00:34:24,319 --> 00:34:25,453
Losing your way...

498
00:34:27,222 --> 00:34:28,423
only takes a moment.

499
00:34:31,126 --> 00:34:32,794
Anyway, I've delivered the message.

500
00:34:33,828 --> 00:34:35,764
Let's see how different you are...

501
00:34:37,899 --> 00:34:38,800
from me.

502
00:34:59,254 --> 00:35:02,824
(Mr. Bae)

503
00:35:18,506 --> 00:35:19,541
No.

504
00:35:20,275 --> 00:35:21,142
Okay.

505
00:35:27,115 --> 00:35:29,718
I want to rethink my life.

506
00:35:37,158 --> 00:35:38,093
Don't waver.

507
00:35:39,494 --> 00:35:40,395
Don't waver.

508
00:35:41,730 --> 00:35:43,098
I can't afford to waver too.

509
00:35:43,798 --> 00:35:45,367
Cho Mi Ryeo, don't waver.

510
00:35:46,301 --> 00:35:47,335
Don't think.

511
00:36:27,809 --> 00:36:31,179
Ji Cheon, this is your first time
in a place like Yeonri-ri, right?

512
00:36:34,616 --> 00:36:36,818
The water's clean, and the air is fresh...

513
00:36:38,820 --> 00:36:40,855
Honestly, I love places like this too.

514
00:36:41,690 --> 00:36:43,725
It's quiet and peaceful.

515
00:36:46,361 --> 00:36:47,562
Mom, I...

516
00:36:48,396 --> 00:36:49,297
But...

517
00:36:53,101 --> 00:36:55,770
the reason this place feels peaceful is...

518
00:36:56,972 --> 00:36:59,074
because you're not from here.

519
00:37:02,310 --> 00:37:04,145
It's nice when you're just visiting.

520
00:37:05,480 --> 00:37:06,982
That's why they call it a rural getaway.

521
00:37:08,917 --> 00:37:10,986
But what if it becomes one year...

522
00:37:12,087 --> 00:37:13,321
Then two years...

523
00:37:14,623 --> 00:37:16,391
And then five years?

524
00:37:17,459 --> 00:37:21,396
Would it still feel quiet
and peaceful then?

525
00:37:23,765 --> 00:37:27,936
Wouldn't it start to feel suffocating
and frustrating...

526
00:37:29,070 --> 00:37:30,972
like you're trapped?

527
00:37:31,906 --> 00:37:34,609
I'm not saying I'll live here forever.

528
00:37:35,110 --> 00:37:36,845
I just want to figure out who I am...

529
00:37:36,845 --> 00:37:38,146
and what I really want to do in life.

530
00:37:38,146 --> 00:37:40,715
I've never had the time
to think about that before.

531
00:37:42,584 --> 00:37:45,854
And right now, I desperately
need that time.

532
00:37:45,854 --> 00:37:47,122
Once that time passes...

533
00:37:47,122 --> 00:37:47,989
There's something...

534
00:37:48,857 --> 00:37:50,058
even your dad doesn't know.

535
00:37:53,762 --> 00:37:55,497
My hometown...

536
00:37:56,598 --> 00:37:57,732
isn't actually Seoul.

537
00:37:58,700 --> 00:37:59,534
What?

538
00:38:01,369 --> 00:38:04,072
I was born in a rural place like this...

539
00:38:05,607 --> 00:38:07,175
and grew up there
until I was in middle school.

540
00:38:09,611 --> 00:38:12,080
There was nowhere else to study
except school.

541
00:38:13,081 --> 00:38:13,982
I couldn't even dare...

542
00:38:14,916 --> 00:38:17,953
to dream big.

543
00:38:20,221 --> 00:38:22,557
When I first went to Seoul,

544
00:38:22,958 --> 00:38:24,292
I was really shocked.

545
00:38:26,127 --> 00:38:28,229
There were so many opportunities.

546
00:38:30,198 --> 00:38:32,801
But I realized it...

547
00:38:34,202 --> 00:38:35,737
too late.

548
00:38:38,640 --> 00:38:41,977
I struggled so hard to catch up
with everyone else.

549
00:38:44,145 --> 00:38:45,780
That's when I met your dad.

550
00:38:47,482 --> 00:38:49,384
And when I had you,

551
00:38:51,252 --> 00:38:52,587
I made a decision.

552
00:38:53,989 --> 00:38:55,657
That I would create...

553
00:38:57,025 --> 00:39:00,095
countless opportunities for my child.

554
00:39:00,695 --> 00:39:01,563
And...

555
00:39:02,597 --> 00:39:06,267
make sure you could always
choose the best path.

556
00:39:07,002 --> 00:39:08,837
Mom, I...

557
00:39:08,837 --> 00:39:10,038
I know you're struggling.

558
00:39:11,673 --> 00:39:14,075
It can't be easy to constantly compete...

559
00:39:14,743 --> 00:39:17,012
among the best of the best.

560
00:39:19,147 --> 00:39:20,215
But Ji Cheon...

561
00:39:22,217 --> 00:39:24,452
You've come this far already.

562
00:39:25,620 --> 00:39:26,655
Just a few more years...

563
00:39:27,589 --> 00:39:29,524
Take the board exam.

564
00:39:30,392 --> 00:39:32,494
Even then, if it still doesn't feel right,

565
00:39:33,695 --> 00:39:35,730
we'll reconsider, okay?

566
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:42,971
I would never do anything that harms you.

567
00:39:44,973 --> 00:39:46,241
You know that.

568
00:39:49,711 --> 00:39:52,147
Let's go back, son.

569
00:39:53,448 --> 00:39:54,316
Please?

570
00:40:03,825 --> 00:40:04,993
It's too cold out here.

571
00:40:05,393 --> 00:40:07,495
Don't stay out too long, okay?

572
00:40:24,446 --> 00:40:25,313
Seriously...

573
00:40:31,119 --> 00:40:32,220
How long...

574
00:40:33,989 --> 00:40:36,658
are you going to keep
choosing my life for me?

575
00:41:13,595 --> 00:41:16,197
They say joy doubles when shared,

576
00:41:17,132 --> 00:41:19,534
and sorrow is cut in half.

577
00:41:22,604 --> 00:41:24,973
Can't he lean on me a little too?

578
00:41:28,843 --> 00:41:30,578
Ji Cheon is being too harsh.

579
00:41:45,860 --> 00:41:47,395
Coffee's over there.

580
00:41:49,864 --> 00:41:51,199
Enjoy.

581
00:41:51,199 --> 00:41:52,901
- Please enjoy.
- Thank you.

582
00:42:06,982 --> 00:42:07,849
Hye Sun.

583
00:42:08,516 --> 00:42:09,617
Shouldn't you ask her?

584
00:42:11,052 --> 00:42:11,920
No.

585
00:42:12,954 --> 00:42:14,089
There's nothing to ask.

586
00:42:15,490 --> 00:42:17,325
I know what I saw.

587
00:42:23,431 --> 00:42:25,834
(No notifications)

588
00:42:31,473 --> 00:42:33,208
Does somebody owe you money or something?

589
00:42:33,708 --> 00:42:35,610
You've been staring at your phone all day.

590
00:42:35,610 --> 00:42:36,678
Do you have something special in there?

591
00:42:37,078 --> 00:42:37,912
Me?

592
00:42:39,247 --> 00:42:40,882
What did I do?

593
00:42:41,483 --> 00:42:43,885
You...

594
00:42:44,853 --> 00:42:47,155
The eldest son of Mat Story...

595
00:42:47,789 --> 00:42:49,291
What about him?

596
00:42:49,557 --> 00:42:52,694
How long has he been working
at the school?

597
00:42:55,764 --> 00:42:57,299
It's been a while.

598
00:42:57,299 --> 00:42:58,133
Right?

599
00:43:00,235 --> 00:43:01,536
Yes.

600
00:43:01,770 --> 00:43:03,738
The cook said she had too much work, so...

601
00:43:04,506 --> 00:43:07,108
He's good and learns fast.

602
00:43:07,108 --> 00:43:08,677
He's been a big help too.

603
00:43:09,944 --> 00:43:12,981
I guess he's going back to Seoul soon.

604
00:43:12,981 --> 00:43:13,815
What?

605
00:43:14,282 --> 00:43:15,250
When?

606
00:43:16,051 --> 00:43:17,986
He said he wouldn't go
if I told him not to.

607
00:43:17,986 --> 00:43:19,154
Im Bo Mi.

608
00:43:19,154 --> 00:43:21,089
Is there actually something going on
between you two?

609
00:43:21,089 --> 00:43:23,058
Why would he do what you tell him to do?

610
00:43:24,092 --> 00:43:25,393
Well...

611
00:43:25,860 --> 00:43:26,761
You see...

612
00:43:27,462 --> 00:43:28,430
The part-time job.

613
00:43:28,897 --> 00:43:31,099
When I hired him,

614
00:43:31,099 --> 00:43:32,834
he promised to work for
at least one semester.

615
00:43:33,368 --> 00:43:35,303
Get your head on straight, okay?

616
00:43:35,303 --> 00:43:37,839
Unless you want to see your dad
clutch his neck and collapse.

617
00:43:37,839 --> 00:43:39,574
That wouldn't be all.

618
00:43:39,574 --> 00:43:42,243
He'll start World War II with Mat Story.

619
00:43:44,012 --> 00:43:46,681
I think we're out of milk.

620
00:43:46,681 --> 00:43:47,582
Let me check.

621
00:43:50,085 --> 00:43:50,952
Yes, we're out.

622
00:43:51,453 --> 00:43:52,821
Mom. It's time to make
some lemon syrup too.

623
00:43:52,821 --> 00:43:53,955
I'll go buy some lemons.

624
00:43:54,155 --> 00:43:56,358
We're out of sugar too. Get some of that.

625
00:43:56,358 --> 00:43:57,792
All right.

626
00:43:58,727 --> 00:43:59,761
I'll be back soon.

627
00:44:05,533 --> 00:44:07,869
She's being foolish.

628
00:44:08,603 --> 00:44:09,738
That idiot.

629
00:44:10,972 --> 00:44:12,307
I wonder who she takes after.

630
00:44:12,641 --> 00:44:13,708
This is trouble.

631
00:44:14,542 --> 00:44:15,877
You look way too excited.

632
00:44:17,078 --> 00:44:17,979
That's not true.

633
00:44:21,916 --> 00:44:23,952
Why do you look so fresh?

634
00:44:28,590 --> 00:44:31,259
Im Bo Mi. Why do you have
such bad taste in men?

635
00:44:42,037 --> 00:44:42,837
Bo Mi?

636
00:44:46,574 --> 00:44:47,809
You're busy even on the weekend.

637
00:44:49,577 --> 00:44:51,212
I'm running an errand for the cafe.

638
00:44:51,212 --> 00:44:52,714
You need to buy lemons?

639
00:44:52,981 --> 00:44:53,982
How many?

640
00:44:53,982 --> 00:44:55,383
What else do you need?

641
00:44:55,383 --> 00:44:58,286
Just sugar and a few other things.

642
00:44:58,286 --> 00:44:59,521
Is this enough?

643
00:45:00,188 --> 00:45:01,022
Yes.

644
00:45:06,061 --> 00:45:06,928
This is great.

645
00:45:07,562 --> 00:45:09,097
Let's shop for groceries together.

646
00:45:10,365 --> 00:45:13,668
Teach me how to pick fresh ingredients.

647
00:45:13,668 --> 00:45:16,004
I'll carry everything back
to the cafe for you.

648
00:45:20,008 --> 00:45:22,844
You're kind as always, Officer Park.

649
00:45:24,579 --> 00:45:27,082
Hearing you say that makes me happy.

650
00:45:29,050 --> 00:45:30,618
Yes, let's shop together.

651
00:45:30,618 --> 00:45:31,753
What do you need?

652
00:45:34,489 --> 00:45:36,758
Carrots, potatoes, and...

653
00:45:42,731 --> 00:45:43,932
You shouldn't buy this.

654
00:45:44,599 --> 00:45:46,201
It is visibly wilted.

655
00:45:46,201 --> 00:45:47,602
If you eat this, you'll probably get sick.

656
00:45:48,403 --> 00:45:49,337
Don't get this one.

657
00:45:49,838 --> 00:45:52,173
Grab all the heavy stuff since I'm here.

658
00:45:53,174 --> 00:45:54,843
Okay. Thanks.

659
00:45:55,477 --> 00:45:56,544
No problem.

660
00:46:01,116 --> 00:46:02,083
Potatoes.

661
00:46:12,627 --> 00:46:14,929
Are you two dating?

662
00:46:15,297 --> 00:46:16,731
You look like newlyweds.

663
00:46:17,232 --> 00:46:18,199
Thank you.

664
00:46:19,267 --> 00:46:21,069
It's not like that.

665
00:46:21,069 --> 00:46:22,837
Come on.

666
00:46:22,837 --> 00:46:23,972
You two look great together.

667
00:46:24,506 --> 00:46:26,708
Don't go around saying weird things.
It's not true.

668
00:46:26,708 --> 00:46:28,109
You two look great together.

669
00:46:32,480 --> 00:46:34,015
Bo Mi, watch your step here.

670
00:46:34,015 --> 00:46:34,783
Okay.

671
00:47:04,479 --> 00:47:05,847
I miss Bo Mi.

672
00:47:18,126 --> 00:47:20,261
I miss you, Bo Mi.

673
00:47:34,142 --> 00:47:36,311
I can't even quit school properly.

674
00:47:46,087 --> 00:47:47,689
Honey, you're home.

675
00:47:47,689 --> 00:47:49,324
I'm going to bed now.

676
00:47:49,324 --> 00:47:50,625
Can you take care of the rest?

677
00:47:50,625 --> 00:47:51,760
Okay. Go on in.

678
00:48:02,871 --> 00:48:03,605
Son.

679
00:48:05,373 --> 00:48:06,241
Have a seat.

680
00:48:19,054 --> 00:48:20,455
I heard Mom didn't go to the hospital.

681
00:48:21,089 --> 00:48:22,524
Did you get a chance to talk to her?

682
00:48:23,625 --> 00:48:25,593
I couldn't. But she did.

683
00:48:27,128 --> 00:48:29,497
Mom told me to take
the board exam at least...

684
00:48:29,497 --> 00:48:30,765
and think about the rest afterward.

685
00:48:36,671 --> 00:48:37,539
Dad.

686
00:48:40,175 --> 00:48:41,309
I'm wavering.

687
00:48:43,044 --> 00:48:45,847
Just like that? When you were
so firm before?

688
00:48:50,885 --> 00:48:54,122
This is the first decision
I've ever made for myself.

689
00:48:56,324 --> 00:48:57,525
I was confident too.

690
00:49:01,096 --> 00:49:01,930
But...

691
00:49:02,797 --> 00:49:04,666
now that you and Mom
are saying the same thing,

692
00:49:06,668 --> 00:49:09,604
I'm scared that I might be...

693
00:49:11,272 --> 00:49:12,307
making the wrong choice.

694
00:49:19,714 --> 00:49:20,515
Son.

695
00:49:22,717 --> 00:49:24,185
Every choice...

696
00:49:24,953 --> 00:49:26,488
comes with responsibility.

697
00:49:26,921 --> 00:49:27,756
You know that, right?

698
00:49:29,758 --> 00:49:31,626
Even at my age,

699
00:49:32,060 --> 00:49:34,629
I still get scared sometimes...

700
00:49:34,629 --> 00:49:35,697
that I might choose the wrong path.

701
00:49:36,931 --> 00:49:38,433
But once you make a decision,

702
00:49:39,100 --> 00:49:40,669
you can't look back.

703
00:49:42,270 --> 00:49:43,438
Even if you regret it,

704
00:49:43,905 --> 00:49:46,474
it's better to face it head-on
and regret it.

705
00:49:46,908 --> 00:49:49,844
If you don't try, your chance
of success is 0%.

706
00:49:50,445 --> 00:49:52,781
If you do, it's 50%.

707
00:51:10,091 --> 00:51:12,494
Bo Mi, I'm going to Seoul.

708
00:51:30,078 --> 00:51:34,015
We received the croissant sauce you sent.

709
00:51:34,015 --> 00:51:35,483
Yes, that's right.

710
00:51:35,483 --> 00:51:37,452
Thank you.

711
00:51:39,487 --> 00:51:42,290
I'm sorry. I was on another call.

712
00:51:42,290 --> 00:51:44,893
The delivery... Can you send it
in about 30 minutes?

713
00:51:46,294 --> 00:51:48,496
Thank you. All right.

714
00:51:53,168 --> 00:51:55,270
Hi. Burdock root...

715
00:51:55,270 --> 00:51:56,871
One box is missing.

716
00:51:57,839 --> 00:51:58,907
Yes.

717
00:51:58,907 --> 00:52:01,710
All right. Thank you.

718
00:52:05,981 --> 00:52:07,382
(Order Sheet)

719
00:52:07,382 --> 00:52:09,684
It's absolute chaos
when I have to order ingredients.

720
00:52:17,325 --> 00:52:19,761
Bo Mi, I'm going to Seoul.

721
00:52:41,983 --> 00:52:42,851
Bo Mi.

722
00:52:54,195 --> 00:52:55,397
Ji Cheon.

723
00:52:55,397 --> 00:52:57,932
You need to leave early
to go see your professor.

724
00:52:57,932 --> 00:53:00,035
Dad said he'd take you.

725
00:53:12,314 --> 00:53:13,081
Ji Cheon.

726
00:53:29,397 --> 00:53:30,198
Honey.

727
00:53:30,598 --> 00:53:31,766
Ji Cheon isn't here.

728
00:53:33,168 --> 00:53:35,136
Did he leave for the interview already?

729
00:53:35,971 --> 00:53:37,339
Get dressed quickly.

730
00:53:37,339 --> 00:53:39,074
I need to go after him.

731
00:53:39,074 --> 00:53:40,408
Honey.

732
00:53:40,408 --> 00:53:43,178
I'm sure Ji Cheon will make a good choice.

733
00:53:43,178 --> 00:53:44,479
Let's trust him and wait.

734
00:53:44,479 --> 00:53:46,748
I told you I'd handle
the kids' matters myself.

735
00:53:46,748 --> 00:53:47,582
No.

736
00:53:48,516 --> 00:53:49,317
I am...

737
00:53:50,151 --> 00:53:50,952
their father too.

738
00:53:50,952 --> 00:53:54,456
You can't hold onto
a grown child forever.

739
00:53:56,992 --> 00:53:58,493
Let go, okay?

740
00:53:58,960 --> 00:54:01,696
We need to start practicing that now.

741
00:54:15,143 --> 00:54:17,779
(Mat Story)

742
00:54:34,229 --> 00:54:36,197
I sent you a little gift.

743
00:54:38,533 --> 00:54:40,402
A gift?

744
00:54:41,636 --> 00:54:42,504
Mr. Choi.

745
00:54:43,438 --> 00:54:44,572
The sample analysis report.

746
00:54:47,409 --> 00:54:48,877
You were told to sign it,

747
00:54:48,877 --> 00:54:50,111
but you haven't done so yet.

748
00:54:50,779 --> 00:54:51,813
What are you hesitating for?

749
00:54:53,048 --> 00:54:56,484
You're the one who will be moving
into the office here right below mine.

750
00:55:01,957 --> 00:55:04,326
Mr. Choi's position will soon be vacant.

751
00:55:05,160 --> 00:55:06,895
If you choose to stand on my side.

752
00:55:08,430 --> 00:55:11,232
I won't take anyone's side.

753
00:55:13,301 --> 00:55:15,437
My job is to focus on cabbage research.
Nothing else.

754
00:55:16,204 --> 00:55:17,405
And for Mat Story,

755
00:55:17,405 --> 00:55:19,274
I've given it my full sincerity.

756
00:55:28,717 --> 00:55:30,785
That's what I like about you, Mr. Seong.

757
00:55:31,886 --> 00:55:33,421
Faith and honesty.

758
00:55:34,122 --> 00:55:36,057
Those are Mat Story's core values.

759
00:55:37,692 --> 00:55:39,160
You're diligent and steadfast.

760
00:55:40,095 --> 00:55:42,263
Where else would we find someone like you?

761
00:55:43,898 --> 00:55:46,801
I will rewrite the report.

762
00:55:47,235 --> 00:55:50,005
Based on facts with reliable data.

763
00:55:50,872 --> 00:55:52,607
Yes, of course.

764
00:55:53,475 --> 00:55:55,644
There must've been some mistake.

765
00:55:56,311 --> 00:55:58,680
Of course, it should be written
based on facts.

766
00:55:58,680 --> 00:55:59,914
Follow your convictions.

767
00:56:04,185 --> 00:56:05,053
To be honest,

768
00:56:06,154 --> 00:56:08,290
I don't really understand your intentions.

769
00:56:09,424 --> 00:56:10,659
From what I've heard in Yeonri-ri,

770
00:56:11,326 --> 00:56:13,728
Mat Story has done some bad things.

771
00:56:14,663 --> 00:56:16,931
I kept denying it,

772
00:56:16,931 --> 00:56:19,367
but after seeing this failed test report,

773
00:56:20,235 --> 00:56:22,570
I'm very conflicted.

774
00:56:24,973 --> 00:56:26,341
There's no need to be conflicted.

775
00:56:27,175 --> 00:56:30,111
There were indeed some controversies
in the past.

776
00:56:30,578 --> 00:56:32,047
But with your assignment,

777
00:56:32,547 --> 00:56:35,550
Yeonri-ri and Mat Story will move forward
in mutual growth.

778
00:56:36,584 --> 00:56:37,385
What do you say?

779
00:56:38,019 --> 00:56:40,689
Will you stand with me from now on?

780
00:56:45,794 --> 00:56:48,063
May I ask about...

781
00:56:48,997 --> 00:56:50,365
the new vision you're planning?

782
00:56:59,174 --> 00:57:00,542
Before I answer that,

783
00:57:01,376 --> 00:57:04,379
I need you to swear
absolute loyalty to me.

784
00:57:06,281 --> 00:57:07,382
Can you personally prove...

785
00:57:08,717 --> 00:57:10,518
that this path will save the village...

786
00:57:15,957 --> 00:57:19,060
and my family?

787
00:57:23,331 --> 00:57:26,067
Of course. I promise.

788
00:57:37,078 --> 00:57:38,613
A good fountain pen...

789
00:57:39,180 --> 00:57:41,850
helps you make good decisions.

790
00:57:43,018 --> 00:57:43,918
Take it.

791
00:58:02,537 --> 00:58:03,872
Maybe a choice...

792
00:58:14,049 --> 00:58:16,518
isn't about right or wrong.

793
00:58:24,659 --> 00:58:26,428
Maybe it's about taking responsibility...

794
00:58:33,902 --> 00:58:37,172
for the path you can't come back from.

795
00:59:04,799 --> 00:59:07,669
(Cabbage Your Life)

796
00:59:07,669 --> 00:59:08,837
This is all because of you.

797
00:59:08,837 --> 00:59:10,772
The more you act like this,
the more suffocated I feel.

798
00:59:10,772 --> 00:59:13,842
So I've been the one suffocating
the whole family?

799
00:59:13,842 --> 00:59:15,744
- Let's see how you all do without me.
- Honey.

800
00:59:15,744 --> 00:59:17,078
Where's Mom?

801
00:59:17,078 --> 00:59:18,580
This isn't right.

802
00:59:18,580 --> 00:59:19,481
Let's go find Mom.

803
00:59:19,481 --> 00:59:21,349
Where is she?

804
00:59:21,349 --> 00:59:22,450
Look. It's Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.

805
00:59:22,450 --> 00:59:24,853
How can I run into them here?

806
00:59:24,853 --> 00:59:26,021
I'm sorry, Bo Mi.

807
00:59:26,021 --> 00:59:26,955
Ji Cheon.

808
00:59:26,955 --> 00:59:28,757
If you're going to be like this,
let's quit now.

809
00:59:28,757 --> 00:59:30,025
Is it because of Ji Cheon?

810
00:59:30,025 --> 00:59:31,693
I would never make the woman I like cry.

811
00:59:31,693 --> 00:59:32,827
Why would Mat Story do that?

812
00:59:32,827 --> 00:59:34,562
They're up to something.

813
00:59:34,562 --> 00:59:35,864
What? Where?

814
00:59:36,264 --> 00:59:38,266
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
